<h2 id="projects">Projects</h2>

<p><strong>9</strong>. <a href="/tgd">Affective States and Online Teaching in Chemistry Education</a> (2020 - Present)</p>

<ul>
  <li>This project has just initiated and is currently at the literature review phase.</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>8</strong>. <a href="/gbv">Integrating learning objects into D2L to promote student learning of difficult scientific concepts</a> (2017 - 2018)</p>

<ul>
  <li>This project focuses on the development of a learning object dealing with the ‚Äúparticle in a box‚Äù (PIAB) model of quantum mechanics.</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>7</strong>. <a href="/drc">Alternative assessment method in biochemistry education: Graphical representation of oxygen binding and delivery</a> (2017 - 2018)</p>

<ul>
  <li>This project focuses on how to measure students‚Äô conceptual understanding in the context of undergraduate biochemistry course at DePaul University.</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>6</strong>. <a href="/zhm">Impact of instructional interactivity in chemistry education</a> (2015 - 2016)</p>

<ul>
  <li>IIICE Project aims to integrate student response systems (SRS) into undergraduate general chemistry courses.</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>5</strong>. <a href="/upv">Workshop for in-service science teachers</a> (January 2014)</p>

<ul>
  <li>This project involved secondary in-service science teachers, having the content areas of chemistry, physics, biology, and mathematics, to advance their practicals skill on project development in education as way of improved teaching practice.</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>4</strong>. <a href="/dgq">Pedagogical discontentment and self-efficacy of science teachers</a> (2013 - 2015)</p>

<ul>
  <li>The Science Teachers‚Äô Pedagogical Discontentment (STPD) scale has formerly been developed in the United States and used since 2006. Based on the perceptions of selected teachers, the scale is deeply rooted in the cultural and national standards.</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>3</strong>. <a href="/vzm">Physical chemistry education and learning objects</a> (2012 - 2014)</p>

<ul>
  <li>PChemLO project aims at measuring students‚Äô alternative conceptions in the context of physical chemistry course, which is enriched by educational technology.</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>2</strong>. <a href="/rqj">Applying research on science materials implementation: Bringing measurement of fidelity of implementation (FOI) to scale</a> (2007 - 2008)</p>

<ul>
  <li>This is a project for instructional materials development based on applied research and is a three-year study of the implementation of NSF-supported science instructional materials in Chicago.</li>
</ul>

<p><strong>1</strong>. <a href="/vhr">EcoVentures: Focus on the Gulf</a> (2000 - 2001)</p>

<ul>
  <li>EcoVentures: Focus on the Gulf is a multimedia CD designed to help middle school students learn about the Gulf of Mexico‚Äôs aquatic environment and the issues associated with protecting and managing aquatic resources.</li>
</ul>

